  "number": 2557,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2557",
  "title": "urlSync pushes new history state on load if searchFunction is used",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nBug\r\n\r\nCode is here, urlSync seems not to work with jsfiddle:\r\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/9n8Lnqas/\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\nWhen instant search is created and the query is modified by searchFunction, urlSync pushes a new state to history on load. This behavior was implemented in v2.2.2 with a fix for #2530 \r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\nPrevious to version 2.2.2, urlSync only pushes new states after user interaction with instantsearch. If new states are being created in browser history on load, this poses a problem for sites with catalog views that utilize instantsearch. In our case, thousands of pages are immediately appended with instantsearch parameters after page/instantsearch loading. We use searchFunction for various facets that are subject to change based other previous user interactions on the site.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nAll browsers that support the history API when urlSync option is used.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\nThere may be a better way to resolve issue #2530 , or maybe additional urlSync options could make this configurable.\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\nv2.2.2 Currently using 2.2.1 to get around this.\r\n\r\n<!-- Delete any HTML comment and non relevant questions -->\r\n",
